Date: 0/0/1947
Source: Native Animals of NZ
Author: POWELL
Vol / Page: 28
Edition:
Quote: WHITE ROCK SHELL (<i>Neothais scalaris</i>). Hopetea of the Maoris. A thick, coarse spirally ridged white shell up to 3 a inches in height. It is common amongst rocks at low tide, both in harbours and on the open coast. The species is widespread in New Zealand and occurs in Tasmania and Southern Australia also.
